Pamodzi Gold’s Mining Assets Put Up for Sale by South African Liquidator

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-06-21T05:29:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/pamodzi-gold-s-mining-assets-put-up-for-sale-by-south-african-liquidator.html
Pamodzi Gold Ltd. (PZG) ’s mining assets in
 South Africa  have been put up for sale, the company’s joint
liquidators said.  Pamodzi’s Orkney, Modderfontein, Grootvlei, Nigel and East
Rand operations are to be sold after being placed under
provisional liquidation in 2009, the liquidators said in two
advertisements published in the Johannesburg-based Business Day
newspaper today.  Interested parties have until 5 p.m. local time on June 30
to submit their expressions of interest, according to the
advertisements.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  